{"type":"message","id":"d2b5ac35","parentId":"437fec9b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:08:26.735Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qwolt4ns7tni_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 090408\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. The big pending task is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n3. Next action is: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete, actionable item is to implement the TIC classifier. This is a new experiment that tests the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Analyzes invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n4. Measures accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nI'll create a `tic_experiment.py` file that does this analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic_experiment.py` - a Python script that reads pulse logs, extracts invariant/variant patterns, classifies them, and tests next-pulse prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef parse_pulse_metadata(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract metadata from pulse filename.\"\"\"\r\n    match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(filepath.name)\r\n    if match:\r\n        return {\"date\": match.group(1), \"time\": match.group(2)}\r\n    return None\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_features(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural features from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    try:\r\n        with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n            content = f.read()\r\n        \r\n        features = {\r\n            \"length\": len(content),\r\n            \"sections\": len(re.findall(r\"^#{1,3}\\s+\", content, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n            \"bullet_points\": len(re.findall(r\"^\\s*[-*]\\s+\", content, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n            \"has_observation\": bool(re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\", content)),\r\n            \"has_action\": bool(re.search(r\"### ACTION\", content)),\r\n            \"has_mutation\": bool(re.search(r\"### MUTATION\", content)),\r\n            \"code_blocks\": len(re.findall(r\"```\", content)) // 2,\r\n            \"mutations_applied\": \"No mutations applied\" not in content and \"file:\" in content.lower(),\r\n        }\r\n        return features\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        print(f\"Error reading {filepath}: {e}\")\r\n        return None\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Identify invariant patterns across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses) < 2:\r\n        return {}, {}\r\n    \r\n    # Features that rarely change = invariants\r\n    invariant_candidates = [\"has_observation\", \"has_action\", \"has_mutation\", \"sections\"]\r\n    \r\n    # Count values across pulses\r\n    invariant_features = {}\r\n    variant_features = {}\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        features = pulse[\"features\"]\r\n        for feat in features:\r\n            if feat not in invariant_features:\r\n                invariant_features[feat] = []\r\n            invariant_features[feat].append(features[feat])\r\n    \r\n    # Classify: low variance = invariant, high variance = variant\r\n    for feat, values in invariant_features.items():\r\n        if len(values) < 2:\r\n            continue\r\n        value_counts = Counter(values)\r\n        most_common_pct = value_counts.most_common(1)[0][1] / len(values)\r\n        \r\n        if most_common_pct > 0.8:  # Stable across 80%+ pulses\r\n            feat_type = \"invariant\"\r\n        elif most_common_pct < 0.5:  # Changes frequently\r\n            feat_type = \"variant\"\r\n        else:\r\n            feat_type = \"mixed\"\r\n        \r\n        if feat in invariant_candidates or feat_type == \"invariant\":\r\n            invariant_features[feat] = {\"type\": \"invariant\", \"stability\": most_common_pct}\r\n        else:\r\n            variant_features[feat] = {\"type\": \"variant\", \"stability\": most_common_pct}\r\n    \r\n    return invariant_features, variant_features\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulse(pulse, invariants, variants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a pulse's features as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    features = pulse[\"features\"]\r\n    results = {\"invariant\": [], \"variant\": []}\r\n    \r\n    for feat, value in features.items():\r\n        if feat in invariants:\r\n            results[\"invariant\"].append(feat)\r\n        elif feat in variants:\r\n            results[\"variant\"].append(feat)\r\n    \r\n    return results\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(prev_pulse, next_pulse, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse features from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    prev_features = prev_pulse[\"features\"]\r\n    \r\n    predictions = {}\r\n    for invariant_feat in invariants:\r\n        if invariant_feat in prev_features:\r\n            predictions[invariant_feat] = prev_features[invariant_feat]\r\n    \r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_prediction(predictions, actual):\r\n    \"\"\"Evaluate prediction accuracy.\"\"\"\r\n    if not predictions:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    correct\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:04:41"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":833,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 090408\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. The big pending task is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n3. Next action is: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete, actionable item is to implement the TIC classifier. This is a new experiment that tests the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Analyzes invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n4. Measures accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nI'll create a `tic_experiment.py` file that does this analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic_experiment.py` - a Python script that reads pulse logs, extracts invariant/variant patterns, classifies them, and tests next-pulse prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/b